<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-01T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-01T21:00:00-05:00" n="313" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d313">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">862.01/8–21744: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-01T22:00:00-04:00">September 1,
                                1944—10 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>2430. The question of whether or not Germany is to be partitioned is
                        currently under consideration and has not yet been decided.<note n="97" xml:id="d313fn97">For correspondence on the problem of the partition of
                            Germany, see <ref target="#pg_161">pp. 161</ref>–<ref target="#pg_166">166</ref>, <ref target="#pg_274">274</ref>, <ref target="#pg_303">303</ref>, <ref target="#pg_311">311</ref>–<ref target="#pg_312">312</ref>, <ref target="#pg_345">345</ref>, and <ref target="#pg_359">359</ref>.</note> It appears, however, that the
                        territorial arrangement outlined in your SS–2, August 27, 5 p.m., would not
                        fit in with Allied plans in so far as they have been formulated up to the
                        present time.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>